Responce returns the data of recent adjustments.</br>
To specify the time range, change the number of minutes in the **Pre-req** tab:

    var n = 240; //specify number of minutes (look up data for last N minutes)

The result is printed in the console in the format:</br>

    {"product":"00077901008589","address":"01K","comment":"PO=2103091897737","temperature-zone":"chilled"}

Response returns the data of recent adjustments.</br>
To specify the time range, change the number of minutes in the **Pre-req** tab:

    var n = 5; //specify number of minutes (look up data for last N minutes)

Change the product to look for in array: 

    //specify products to look for adjustments
    var products = ["123"];
    pm.collectionVariables.set("products", products);

The result is printed in the console in the format:</br>

    00000000091688, chilled: {"address":"01K","qty-before":8,"qty":-1,"comment":"ORDER=29571874;","qty-now":7}

